PILLAR 1: Performance & State Management
1.1 WebSocket — Memory Leak on Reconnect
File: CryptoForge/engine/ws_feed.py:354-356


# Auto-reconnect
if self._running:
    print("[WS] Initiating reconnect...")
    asyncio.create_task(self._do_connect())   # ← PROBLEM
_reader_loop's finally block fires asyncio.create_task(_do_connect()) while the old _reader_task and _heartbeat_task instance variables still point to the exiting tasks. The new _do_connect() overwrites self._reader_task and self._heartbeat_task on its next successful connection — but it does not cancel the old references before overwriting. Under rapid reconnect cycles (network flapping) this creates orphaned tasks that hold the aiohttp.ClientSession open, accumulating until the process memory is exhausted.

Fix:


# In _reader_loop finally block, before spawning reconnect:
if self._heartbeat_task and not self._heartbeat_task.done():
    self._heartbeat_task.cancel()
if self._ws and not self._ws.closed:
    await self._ws.close()
if self._session and not self._session.closed:
    await self._session.close()
    self._session = None          # force fresh session on reconnect
if self._running:
    asyncio.create_task(self._do_connect())
