3.3 HIGH — runs.json Concurrent Write Race Condition
File: New_Algo/app.py and CryptoForge/app.py

runs.json and strategies.json are read-modify-written by multiple code paths (backtest completion, engine start/stop, shutdown hook) without file locking. Under concurrent requests, two paths can read the same stale version, each append their entry, and the last write wins — losing the other entry.

AlgoForge uses fcntl.flock for the token file but not for runs.json. Apply the same pattern:


import fcntl, tempfile, os

def _save_runs_safe(runs: list):
    lock_path = os.path.join(_HERE, ".runs.lock")
    with open(lock_path, "w") as lock_f:
        fcntl.flock(lock_f, fcntl.LOCK_EX)
        try:
            fd, tmp = tempfile.mkstemp(dir=_HERE, suffix=".tmp")
            with os.fdopen(fd, "w") as f:
                json.dump(runs, f, indent=2, default=str)
            os.replace(tmp, "runs.json")
        finally:
            fcntl.flock(lock_f, fcntl.LOCK_UN)
